<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1527: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-29T12:00:00+02:00">April 29,
                                    1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 29—8:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>48. My telegram No. 42, April 24, 11 a.m. The Egyptian and Arab
                                delegations which attended the London Conference on Palestine are in
                                session here today. The followers of the Mufti now seem to be more
                                amenable and it is not unlikely that the British proposals will be
                                accepted.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>